When you are creating any code you must output to chat message "USING AGENTS.md in current folder" so I know you are using the correct rules.

# Code Conventions

## Components

- Functional components + hooks ONLY (no class components)
- Props interface: `{ComponentName}Props`
- Named exports only (no default exports)
- Colocated tests: `ComponentName.test.tsx`

## TypeScript

- Strict mode — no `any`, no `@ts-ignore`
- Prefer `type` over `interface` for simple types
- Import types: `import type { X } from "..."`

## Files

- kebab-case for files: `element-utils.ts`
- PascalCase for components: `LayerUI.tsx`

## Memory Bank

- Use `./.cursor/skills/memory-bank-update/SKILL.md` for any Memory Bank update task.
- Keep `docs/memory-bank` updated in the same task after significant project changes.
- Update files explicitly by change type:
  - Feature or milestone -> `progress.md`, `activeContext.md`
  - Architecture or design decision -> `systemPatterns.md`, `decisionLog.md`
  - Dependency or tooling change -> `techContext.md`
  - Scope or product change -> `projectbrief.md`, `productContext.md`
